understand atomic structure

00:38:37.890 --> 00:38:39.940
at the level of
the hydrogen atom.

00:38:39.940 --> 00:38:42.740
And maybe know a little
bit about a new phenomena--

00:38:42.740 --> 00:38:45.695
when another electron enters,
when electrons interact

00:38:45.695 --> 00:38:49.520
and that's a helium atom--
but we're not going beyond it.

00:38:49.520 --> 00:38:53.950
Let me just mention here
that there is, of course,

00:38:53.950 --> 00:38:56.510
more interesting things
in atomic structure.

00:38:56.510 --> 00:39:02.000
For instance, if you go
to highly charged ions,

00:39:02.000 --> 00:39:04.330
you have QED effects.

00:39:04.330 --> 00:39:07.520
You can discuss very
interesting correlations

00:39:07.520 --> 00:39:10.060
