electrons in an atom.

00:39:12.970 --> 00:39:16.520
And you can have very
relativistic effects

00:39:16.520 --> 00:39:18.420
if you have highly
ionized atoms.

00:39:23.060 --> 00:39:30.970
If you have bare uranium,
then the electron

00:39:30.970 --> 00:39:35.360
in the lowest orbits
becomes relativistic.

00:39:35.360 --> 00:39:38.810
You can even see, if you scale
the fine structure constant--

00:39:38.810 --> 00:39:44.000
which has an e squared in it--
with the charge of uranium 92,

00:39:44.000 --> 00:39:47.110
well, 1 over 137 times
92 gives about 1,

00:39:47.110 --> 00:39:48.900
so you really get
into a new regime

00:39:48.900 --> 00:39:53.120
of coupling for atomic physics.

